  17. (* Pseudo-random number generator *)

  19. external random_seed: unit -> int array = "caml_sys_random_seed"

  21. module State = struct

  23.   open Bigarray

  25.   type t = (int64, int64_elt, c_layout) Array1.t

  27.   external next: t -> (int64[@unboxed])
  28.       = "caml_lxm_next" "caml_lxm_next_unboxed" [@@noalloc]

  30.   let create () : t =
  31.     Array1.create Int64 C_layout 4

  33.   let set s i1 i2 i3 i4 =
  34.     Array1.unsafe_set s 0 (Int64.logor i1 1L); (* must be odd *)
  35.     Array1.unsafe_set s 1 i2;
  36.     Array1.unsafe_set s 2 (if i3 <> 0L then i3 else 1L); (* must not be 0 *)
  37.     Array1.unsafe_set s 3 (if i4 <> 0L then i4 else 2L) (* must not be 0 *)

  39.   let mk i1 i2 i3 i4 =
  40.     let s = create () in
  41.     set s i1 i2 i3 i4; s

  43.   let serialization_prefix =
  44.     "lxm1:"
  45.     (* "lxm" denotes the algorithm currently in use, and '1' is
  46.        a version number. We should update this prefix if we change
  47.        the Random algorithm or the serialization format, so that users
  48.        get a clean error instead of believing that they faithfully
  49.        reproduce their previous state and in fact get a differrent
  50.        stream.

  52.        Note that there is no constraint to keep the same
  53.        "<name><ver>:<data>" format or message size in future versions,
  54.        we could change the format completely if we wanted as long
  55.        as there is no confusion possible with the previous formats. *)

  57.   let serialization_prefix_len =
  58.     String.length serialization_prefix

  60.   let to_binary_string s =
  61.     let prefix = serialization_prefix in
  62.     let preflen = serialization_prefix_len in
  63.     let buf = Bytes.create (preflen + 4 * 8) in
  64.     Bytes.blit_string prefix 0 buf 0 preflen;
  65.     for i = 0 to 3 do
  66.       Bytes.set_int64_le buf (preflen + i * 8) (Array1.get s i)
  67.     done;
  68.     Bytes.unsafe_to_string buf

  70.   let of_binary_string buf =
  71.     let prefix = serialization_prefix in
  72.     let preflen = serialization_prefix_len in
  73.     if String.length buf <> preflen + 4 * 8
  74.        || not (String.starts_with ~prefix buf)
  75.     then
  76.       failwith
  77.         ("Random.State.of_binary_string: expected a format \
  78.           compatible with OCaml " ^ Sys.ocaml_version);
  79.     let i1 = String.get_int64_le buf (preflen + 0 * 8) in
  80.     let i2 = String.get_int64_le buf (preflen + 1 * 8) in
  81.     let i3 = String.get_int64_le buf (preflen + 2 * 8) in
  82.     let i4 = String.get_int64_le buf (preflen + 3 * 8) in
  83.     mk i1 i2 i3 i4

  85.   let assign (dst: t) (src: t) =
  86.     Array1.blit src dst

  88.   let copy s =
  89.     let s' = create() in assign s' s; s'

  91.   (* The seed is an array of integers.  It can be just one integer,
  92.      but it can also be 12 or more bytes.  To hide the difference,
  93.      we serialize the array as a sequence of bytes, then hash the
  94.      sequence with MD5 (Digest.bytes).  MD5 gives only 128 bits while
  95.      we need 256 bits, so we hash twice with different suffixes. *)
  96.   let reinit s seed =
  97.     let n = Array.length seed in
  98.     let b = Bytes.create (n * 8 + 1) in
  99.     for i = 0 to n-1 do
  100.       Bytes.set_int64_le b (i * 8) (Int64.of_int seed.(i))
  101.     done;
  102.     Bytes.set b (n * 8) '\x01';
  103.     let d1 = Digest.bytes b in
  104.     Bytes.set b (n * 8) '\x02';
  105.     let d2 = Digest.bytes b in
  106.     set s (String.get_int64_le d1 0)
  107.           (String.get_int64_le d1 8)
  108.           (String.get_int64_le d2 0)
  109.           (String.get_int64_le d2 8)

  111.   let make seed =
  112.     let s = create() in reinit s seed; s

  114.   let make_self_init () =
  115.     make (random_seed ())

  117.   (* Return 30 random bits as an integer 0 <= x < 1073741824 *)
  118.   let bits s =
  119.     Int64.to_int (next s) land 0x3FFF_FFFF

  121.   (* Return an integer between 0 (included) and [bound] (excluded) *)
  122.   let rec intaux s n =
  123.     let r = bits s in
  124.     let v = r mod n in
  125.     if r - v > 0x3FFFFFFF - n + 1 then intaux s n else v

  127.   let int s bound =
  128.     if bound > 0x3FFFFFFF || bound <= 0
  129.     then invalid_arg "Random.int"
  130.     else intaux s bound

  132.   (* Return an integer between 0 (included) and [bound] (excluded).
  133.      [bound] may be any positive [int]. *)
  134.   let rec int63aux s n =
  135.     let r = Int64.to_int (next s) land max_int in
  136.     let v = r mod n in
  137.     if r - v > max_int - n + 1 then int63aux s n else v

  139.   let full_int s bound =
  140.     if bound <= 0 then
  141.       invalid_arg "Random.full_int"
  142.     else if bound > 0x3FFFFFFF then
  143.       int63aux s bound
  144.     else
  145.       intaux s bound

  147.   (* Return 32 random bits as an [int32] *)
  148.   let bits32 s =
  149.     Int64.to_int32 (next s)

  151.   (* Return an [int32] between 0 (included) and [bound] (excluded). *)
  152.   let rec int32aux s n =
  153.     let r = Int32.shift_right_logical (bits32 s) 1 in
  154.     let v = Int32.rem r n in
  155.     if Int32.(sub r v > add (sub max_int n) 1l)
  156.     then int32aux s n
  157.     else v

  159.   let int32 s bound =
  160.     if bound <= 0l
  161.     then invalid_arg "Random.int32"
  162.     else int32aux s bound

  164.   (* Return 64 random bits as an [int64] *)
  165.   let bits64 s =
  166.     next s

  168.   (* Return an [int64] between 0 (included) and [bound] (excluded). *)
  169.   let rec int64aux s n =
  170.     let r = Int64.shift_right_logical (bits64 s) 1 in
  171.     let v = Int64.rem r n in
  172.     if Int64.(sub r v > add (sub max_int n) 1L)
  173.     then int64aux s n
  174.     else v

  176.   let int64 s bound =
  177.     if bound <= 0L
  178.     then invalid_arg "Random.int64"
  179.     else int64aux s bound

  181.   (* Return 32 or 64 random bits as a [nativeint] *)
  182.   let nativebits =
  183.     if Nativeint.size = 32
  184.     then fun s -> Nativeint.of_int32 (bits32 s)
  185.     else fun s -> Int64.to_nativeint (bits64 s)

  187.   (* Return a [nativeint] between 0 (included) and [bound] (excluded). *)
  188.   let nativeint =
  189.     if Nativeint.size = 32
  190.     then fun s bound -> Nativeint.of_int32 (int32 s (Nativeint.to_int32 bound))
  191.     else fun s bound -> Int64.to_nativeint (int64 s (Int64.of_nativeint bound))

  193.   (* Return a float 0 < x < 1 uniformly distributed among the
  194.      multiples of 2^-53 *)
  195.   let rec rawfloat s =
  196.     let b = next s in
  197.     let n = Int64.shift_right_logical b 11 in
  198.     if n <> 0L then Int64.to_float n *. 0x1.p-53 else rawfloat s

  200.   (* Return a float between 0 and [bound] *)
  201.   let float s bound = rawfloat s *. bound

  203.   (* Return a random Boolean *)
  204.   let bool s = next s < 0L

  206.   (* Split a new PRNG off the given PRNG *)
  207.   let split s =
  208.     let i1 = bits64 s in let i2 = bits64 s in
  209.     let i3 = bits64 s in let i4 = bits64 s in
  210.     mk i1 i2 i3 i4
  211. end
